<kml>
<concept name=Allosteric-Enzyme>

<superconcept name=Allosteric-Protein><hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Allosteric-Enzyme>
  <definition> <conceptref name=Enzyme> that exists in two or more                           conformations depending on the binding of a molecule                           [a ligand] at a <conceptref name=site> other than the catalytic <conceptref name=site>.                          Allosteric enzymes composed of multiple subunits often                          display a cooperative response to ligand binding.                          Alberts:ECB:G-1. </definition>
<seealso name=Allosteric-Protein>
<seealso name=Enzyme>
<seealso name=Regulatory-Site>
<seealso name=Binding-Site>
<seealso name=Active-Site>

</component></kml>
